A couple of thoughts: first, while Infiniband may be better suited to build=
ing the =E2=80=9Csystems=E2=80=9D Huang discusses, the reality is that data=
 centers are built on ethernet, and Nvidia is determined to make that work.=
 Second, the way the company will make that work is through dedicated hardw=
are like its BlueField data processing units; networking hardware used to b=
e specialized, and then it became software-defined on commodity hardware on=
ce performance was good enough. Well, thanks to AI, performance isn=E2=80=
=99t good enough, so specialized hardware is back.

It=E2=80=99s not just networking: when performance isn=E2=80=99t good enoug=
h, either on the edge or the cloud, even as power is a constraint, then har=
dware isn=E2=80=99t a commodity; it=E2=80=99s a differentiator. That sense =
of differentiation and a renewed jostling at every layer of the stack is ve=
ry much in the air here in Taipei, and frankly, relative to nearly all of C=
omputex=E2=80=99s 20 year run, that is unusual; count it as another data po=
int that feels a bit like the 90s (and more on Computex throughout the week=
).

Is AWS Modular or Integrated?
-----------------------------

The goal of Wednesday=E2=80=99s Article AI Integration and Modularization (=
 https://stratechery.com/2024/ai-integration-and-modularization/?access_tok=
en=3DeyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6InN0cmF0ZWNoZXJ5LnBhc3Nwb3J0Lm9ubGluZSIsIn=
